HEADWORD: Shamefast
<hw>Shame"fast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>scamf⟦ae⟧st</ets>.]</ety> <def>Modest; shamefaced.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Shame"fast*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Shame"fast*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> See
<er>Shamefaced</er>.</wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Shamefast</qex> she was in maiden
<qex>shamefastness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Conscience] is a blushing <qex>shamefast</qex> spirit.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Modest apparel with <qex>shamefastness</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Tim.
